                <h1>Understanding the Sugar Act: Key Facts & Impact</h1>
                <p>The Sugar Act of 1764 was a British law imposing taxes on sugar and molasses imported into the American colonies. Aimed at raising revenue and curbing smuggling, it sparked colonial unrest and calls for resistance. This act laid the groundwork for further dissent against British rule, contributing to the American Revolution.</p>
